{
  "texts": [
    "To address this, the system will introduce a genre-adaptive switch that dynamically adjusts module weights through a convolutional neural network (CNN) pre-classifier.",
    "This study evaluates the system's technical advantages through a comparative analysis.",
    "As shown in Table 8, the proposed system outperforms both Grammarly Commercial Version (v5.8) and the GPT-3.5 fine-tuned model in detecting common error types among English as a Second Language learners.",
    "In verb tense correction, the system achieved an F1 score of 93.4%, exceeding Grammarly by 14.2% points.",
    "It also outperformed GPT-3.5 by 9.8% points in article misuse detection, reaching a recall rate of 91.7%."
  ]
}